  ('12eddf4a-c914-4d69-8078-17a5d7ea8b06','becddbcf-bcef-4bb1-80b9-95fed0635545',51.0,'owner ~55 (53-57 band), +4 long-tenure 72yr',70.0,'multi-staff (35 emp) 72yr tenure — solid SBA-financeable book',88.0,'4 strong coasting tells: same shop 1970s-90s (long-tenure tell); social media absent; tell: family-owned; tell: no iso',88.0,'Metro=DFW; nudge +5 (Lockheed/Bell aerospace + general industrial). SBA-financeable buyer access typical.',72.0,'B_forward','Continental Manufacturing (Dallas, TX) — 72yr CNC shop, owner ~55. L1=51 | L2=70 | L3=88 | L4=88 -> final=72 (B_forward). Coasting tells: 4 matched. Enrichment note: B-tier candidate due to PARENT-CO complexity: Continental Manufacturing is a division of Continental NH3 Products (an ag-equipment family business). Any sale would need to detach the captive shop from the parent. NOT a classic solo-owner exit. Buyer would need to negotiate carve-out with the Stretcher/Ward family. A...','certification uplift (ISO 9001 / AS9100) opens aerospace book and lifts margin.','medium',0.78),
  ('21669d87-77d6-4df2-85f6-4486ab994053','becddbcf-bcef-4bb1-80b9-95fed0635545',70.0,'owner ~62 (58-62 band), +4 long-tenure 32yr',70.0,'multi-staff (12 emp) 32yr tenure — solid SBA-financeable book',67.0,'2 coasting tells: same shop 1970s-90s (long-tenure tell); tell: no iso',88.0,'Metro=DFW; nudge +5 (Lockheed/Bell aerospace + general industrial). SBA-financeable buyer access typical.',72.0,'B_forward','Mills Machine Shop Operating Services, Inc. (Ponder, TX) — 32yr CNC shop, owner ~62. L1=70 | L2=70 | L3=67 | L4=88 -> final=72 (B_forward). Coasting tells: 2 matched. Enrichment note: TOP A-tier candidate. Husband-wife co-owners ~62yo + 32yr tenure + no successor + no certifications + rural location = classic small-CNC-shop coasting profile poised for 24-36mo exit. Approach with retirement-focused exit framing.','certification uplift (ISO 9001 / AS9100) opens aerospace book and lifts margin.','medium',0.88),
  ('0a5adfcf-fb7b-4920-9a30-f13b5e3d787c','becddbcf-bcef-4bb1-80b9-95fed0635545',86.0,'owner ~67 (63-67 band), +4 long-tenure 46yr',75.0,'multi-staff (12 emp) 46yr tenure — solid SBA-financeable book; ISO 9001 +5',42.0,'1 coasting tell: same shop 1970s-90s (long-tenure tell)',90.0,'Metro=Houston; nudge +5 (oil+gas+petrochem buyer pool). SBA-financeable buyer access typical.',71.0,'B_forward','S.T.B. Machine Works (Houston, TX) — 46yr CNC shop, owner ~67. L1=86 | L2=75 | L3=42 | L4=90 -> final=71 (B_forward). Certs: ISO 9001. Coasting tells: 1 matched. Enrichment note: STRONG coast signal: website not updated since 2016-2017, 46-yr founder tenure, single ISO cert, modest 11K sqft on 1.3 acres (likely owned). Mazak + HURCO + Haas fleet is solid mid-2000s investment but no recent equipment refresh visible. Acres Homes North Houston — older industrial area. A-TIER CANDIDATE.','operational tightening + ERP/quoting digitization to drive EBITDA uplift.','medium',0.7),
  ('688de3d0-c30e-4d7f-b690-db21f65bbea5','becddbcf-bcef-4bb1-80b9-95fed0635545',70.0,'owner ~62 (58-62 band), +4 long-tenure 37yr',70.0,'multi-staff (25 emp) 37yr tenure — solid SBA-financeable book',67.0,'2 coasting tells: same shop 1970s-90s (long-tenure tell); tell: no certifications',70.0,'Metro=Corpus Christi; nudge 0 (secondary petrochem). SBA-financeable buyer access typical.',69.0,'B_forward','Gulf Coast Repair & Machine Shop, Inc. (Corpus Christi, TX) — 37yr CNC shop, owner ~62. L1=70 | L2=70 | L3=67 | L4=70 -> final=69 (B_forward). Coasting tells: 2 matched. Enrichment note: Owns 20 acres in Corpus Christi — significant real estate. 37-yr tenure under one ownership. NO ISO/AS9100 = either generalist by choice or coasting on legacy customer base. Likely owner approaching retirement age. STRONG ETA TARGET.','certification uplift (ISO 9001 / AS9100) opens aerospace book and lifts margin; diversify into aerospace/defense/medical to de-risk single-cycle exposure.','medium',0.55),
